{"format":"tiptap/v1","updatedAt":"2026-06-21T17:39:12.853Z","doc":{"type":"doc","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Random variables"},{"type":"text","text":" are the fundamental abstraction in probability and statistics that represent uncertain outcomes numerically—they are functions that map the results of random experiments (like coin flips, dice rolls, or measurements) to real numbers, allowing us to quantify and analyze uncertainty mathematically. They form the basis for probability distributions, hypothesis testing, and confidence intervals in machine learning and Generative AI."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"What it is — Clear definition and intuition"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Formal definition:"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"A "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"random variable"},{"type":"text","text":" is a function that maps the outcome of a randomized experiment to a real number."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Notation"},{"type":"text","text":": Typically denoted by capital italicized letters like "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"X"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Y"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Z"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Simple definition"},{"type":"text","text":": A variable where "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"chance determines its value"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conceptual analogy:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Imagine a random process:\n- Coin flip: outcomes = {heads, tails}\n- Dice roll: outcomes = {1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6}\n- Temperature measurement: outcomes = any real number\n\nRandom variable X quantifies these outcomes:\n- X = 1 if heads, X = 0 if tails\n- X = number rolled on dice\n- X = temperature in degrees [web:199][web:205]"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Key insight:"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Random variables are NOT actually \"variables\" that store values"},{"type":"text","text":"—they are "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"functions"},{"type":"text","text":" that assign numerical values to qualitative events so we can analyze them mathematically."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Types of random variables"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"1. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Discrete Random Variables"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Definition"},{"type":"text","text":": Can take on a "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"finite or countable number of values"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Examples"},{"type":"text","text":":\n- Number of heads in 3 coin tosses: X ∈ {0, 1, 2, 3}\n- Dice roll: X ∈ {1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6}\n- Number of customers arriving: X ∈ {0, 1, 2,...}\n- Class label in classification: X ∈ {cat, dog, bird}"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Probability"},{"type":"text","text":": Each value has an associated probability; probabilities sum to 1."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Probability function"},{"type":"text","text":": "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Probability Mass Function (PMF)"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"P(X = x) = probability that X equals x"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Example"},{"type":"text","text":": Fair coin"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"yaml"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"X = 1 if heads, X = 0 if tails\nP(X = 1) = 0.5\nP(X = 0) = 0.5\nSum: 0.5 + 0.5 = 1 ✓"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"2. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Continuous Random Variables"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Definition"},{"type":"text","text":": Can take on an "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"infinite number of values"},{"type":"text","text":" within a range."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Examples"},{"type":"text","text":":\n- Temperature: X ∈ ℝ (any real number)\n- Height: X ∈ [0, ∞)\n- Time until failure: X ∈ [0, ∞)\n- Model weight: X ∈ ℝ"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Probability"},{"type":"text","text":": Infinite outcomes → probability of exact value is 0; use "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"density function"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Probability function"},{"type":"text","text":": "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Probability Density Function (PDF)"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"P(X ∈ [a, b]) = ∫ from a to b of f(x) dx"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Example"},{"type":"text","text":": Normal distribution"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"X ~ Normal(μ=0, σ=1)\nP(X ∈ [-1, 1]) ≈ 0.68 (68% of values fall within 1 standard deviation)"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Quick comparison:"}]},{"type":"table","content":[{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Property"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Discrete"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Continuous"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Values"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Finite/countable"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Infinite (range)"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Probability"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"P(X = x)"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"f(x) (density)"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Function"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"c